#### Q72. What will be the output of this command?

```bash
$ ls -l
file10.txt
file1.txt
fileabc.txt
filea.txt
fileb.txt
filec.txt
$ ls -l file[^abc]*.txt
```

- [x] A

```bash
file1.txt
file10.txt
```

- [ ] B

```bash
file10.txt
file1.txt
fileabc.txt
filea.txt
fileb.txt
filec.txt
```

- [ ] C

```bash
fileabc.txt filea.txt fileb.txt filec.txt
```

- [ ] D

```bash
filea.txt
fileb.txt
filec.txt
```

[Reference](https://tldp.org/LDP/abs/html/globbingref.html)
`The caret (`^`) symbol here negates matches inside the bracket.`

